snippet.textDisplay: the only sushi I would eat from this line-up is Hideyo's spicy tuna roll.  It's a proper 1 BITE sushi.  I feel bad for level 1 but he doesn't make a proper California roll.  Lorenzo has way too much rice on his sushi and put garlic and oil in it (WHAT?).  If you're going to make a tempera roll with avocado on top, you better use eel sauce for sweetness.  A sour/tart sauce won't go well with it.

snippet.textDisplay: Just from looking at the video the first chef messed up by pressing his rice to the plastic mat first instead of the nori.  I just made sushi yesterday because of this video and the moisture from the rice when you press it into the nori helps it stick.  I used a half sheet and it came out great!  I now know that I don't like raddish and I used the wrong cucumber but as far as technique the level 3 chef is spot on.  I didn't even need to use the plastic wrap to cut.  Semi shard knife with slow cutting and a wet blade each time did the trick.  lol Excited about trying new combinations.
